Please let us know if you would like further changes.

@rica Regarding the autoplay. We can allow autoplay when the video is muted. I think we have answered this same issue before?

Chrome's autoplay policies are simple:
  • Muted autoplay is always allowed.
  • Autoplay with sound is allowed if:
    • User has interacted with the domain (click, tap, etc.).
    • On desktop, the user's Media Engagement Index threshold has been crossed, meaning the user has previously played video with sound.
    • The user has added the site to their home screen on mobile or installed the PWA on desktop.
  • Top frames can delegate autoplay permission to their iframes to allow autoplay with sound.

Regarding the images. All good now on that.
@joel can you please take a close look at this? The video elements are set to autoplay but when you go to the website it's not playing automatically. it seems like lazy loading
